&quot;One of the best things about living in a major city are the sleeper&nbsp; 
shows that come our way. Amy Speace, a New York-based singer- 
songwriter is one of the latest. Her sophomore album, &quot;The Killer in&nbsp; 
Me,&quot; a deep, dark album full of lush, emotive lyrics, masterful&nbsp; 
acoustic guitar work and just the right mix of percussion to make up- 
tempo numbers such as &quot;Would I Lie?&quot; rock just right.&quot; - Nancy Dunham,&nbsp; 
Washington Post
